commit_message:
Add  --no-cache-dir to tox command

Because we rely on a horizon master tarball and pip seems
to not be able to detect updates to this tarball, this patch
adds --no-cache-dir to the commands so that pip won't use the cache.

Change-Id: Ic4975c74e6ac0964922132006557f398ec2e25f4

commit_message:
Set initial quota in Quobyte and correct resizing

Ensure a shares initial quota is set in the backend,
and do quota size conversion when resizing.

Closes-Bug: #1771958
Closes-Bug: #1771970

Change-Id: I64a1e591c2682bc8bb62554a95399b5651253f59
(cherry picked from commit fa5c0fd2ce0818a5265141968a719cb38cc383d7)

commit_message:
Fix a no-op network driver bug on plug_port

The base meta-class and no-op network driver had an incorrect plug_port
parameter compared to the allowed-address-pairs driver. This patch corrects
this and aligns the driver signatures.

Change-Id: I74a57ab1374a3cea431fa750aa464d5628e4ef85

commit_message:
import zuul job settings from project-config

This is a mechanically generated patch to complete step 1 of moving
the zuul job settings out of project-config and into each project
repository.

Because there will be a separate patch on each branch, the branch
specifiers for branch-specific jobs have been removed.

Because this patch is generated by a script, there may be some
cosmetic changes to the layout of the YAML file(s) as the contents are
normalized.

See the python3-first goal document for details:
https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/stein/python3-first.html

commit_message:
Handle StopIteration for Py3.7

Catch the raise of StopIteration with return.

PEP 0479, https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0479/, makes the
following change: "when StopIteration is raised inside a generator,
it is replaced it with RuntimeError".
And states: "If raise StopIteration occurs directly in a generator,
simply replace it with return."

Closes-Bug: #1785309
Change-Id: Ib751b680b7357782cb5359526e1e83ee8c5c80dd

Excerpt from chat with amotoki:
=========================================
<amotoki> ????
 Assume the current dhcp opts are [a=x, b=y] and a user want to remove b.
 OSC should provide [a=x] as a new dhcp opts.
<reedip_afk> amotoki : refer [1] . OSC is going to provide [a=x,b=None]       [1]: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/356263/38/openstackclient/network/v2/port.py@942
 for the above test
<amotoki> SDK should check the current dhcp opts and does required API operations.
 i think this is the start line.
<reedip_afk> amotoki : if we pass the current list to neutron, it would remove the DHCP option for "b" , like we discussed earlier
<amotoki> OSC does not need to pass what the neutron API expects.
<amotoki> SDK should be responsible to send the correct API requests and parse API responses.
<reedip_afk> amotoki :  so we have 3 cases (a) Port Create : In this case the list would be empty, so the extra dhcp option would be added
 (b) Port Update [ Add option ] : In this case the list may have one entry, so we need to just add the element to the list
<amotoki> "OSC is going to provide [a=x,b=None]" means a user wants to set None for option 'b'.
 I think you need to clarify what interface SDK provides/should provide.
<reedip_afk> (c): Port Update [ Remove Option ] : means the Option provided would also be an element which also exists in the current DHCP Options list. So we need to set all else to None 
<amotoki> it is related to the design principle. when a back-end API design is a bit tricky, SDK should leak it or hide it.
<amotoki> My stance is the later (hide it and provide a proper abstraction).
========================================='}, {'account_id': 841, 'date': '2017-06-26 12:46:06.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1

I believe individual resource implementation should provide a good abstraction and the proxy layer should provide only convenient methods. The API detail of back-end services should be handled by the resource classes. commit_message:
import zuul job settings from project-config

This is a mechanically generated patch to complete step 1 of moving
the zuul job settings out of project-config and into each project
repository.

Because there will be a separate patch on each branch, the branch
specifiers for branch-specific jobs have been removed.

Because this patch is generated by a script, there may be some
cosmetic changes to the layout of the YAML file(s) as the contents are
normalized.

See the python3-first goal document for details:
https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/stein/python3-first.html

Change-Id: I867d8c58cb49ab5bac892b34c3b761d940f26290
Story: #2002586
Task: #24295

subject: Allow PTLs to not have an IRCnick
reviewers: [{'_account_id': 2, 'name': 'Monty Taylor', 'email': 'mordred@inaugust.com', 'username': 'mordred'}, {'_account_id': 308, 'name': 'Thierry Carrez', 'email': 'thierry@openstack.org', 'username': 'ttx'}, {'_account_id': 1004, 'name': 'Mohammed Naser', 'email': 'mnaser@vexxhost.com', 'username': 'mnaser'}, {'_account_id': 2472, 'name': 'Doug Hellmann', 'email': 'dhellmann@redhat.com', 'username': 'doug-hellmann'}, {'_account_id': 4257, 'name': 'Zane Bitter', 'email': 'zbitter@redhat.com', 'username': 'zaneb'}, {'_account_id': 5263, 'name': 'Jeremy Stanley', 'display_name': 'fungi', 'email': 'fungi@yuggoth.org', 'username': 'fungi', 'status': 'missing, presumed fed'}, {'_account_id': 6088, 'name': 'Emmet Hikory', 'email': 'persia@shipstone.jp', 'username': 'persia'}, {'_account_id': 8482, 'name': 'Colleen Murphy', 'email': 'colleen@gazlene.net', 'username': 'krinkle'}, {'_account_id': 11564, 'name': 'Chris Dent', 'email': 'cdent@anticdent.org', 'username': 'chdent'}, {'_account_id': 12898, 'name': 'Tony Breeds', 'email': 'tony@bakeyournoodle.com', 'username': 'tonyb'}, {'_account_id': 16708, 'name': 'Kendall Nelson', 'display_name': 'Kendall (diablo_rojo)', 'email': 'kennelson11@gmail.com', 'username': 'kjnelson'}, {'_account_id': 22348, 'name': 'Zuul', 'username': 'zuul', 'tags': ['SERVICE_USER']}]
messages:
[{'account_id': 12898, 'date': '2018-08-08 03:53:00.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 1.'}, {'account_id': 11564, 'date': '2018-08-08 08:29:02.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Rollcall-Vote+1 Code-Review+1

(1 comment)

Seems like a good move to me.'}, {'account_id': 5263, 'date': '2018-08-08 13:29:00.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Rollcall-Vote+1'}, {'account_id': 2, 'date': '2018-08-08 13:36:39.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

I don't understand the assertion "at some level it's optional". We are generally pretty adamant that projects use IRC for communication. While I could see IRC being optional for a developer, it seems like once you're PTL of a project you need to have at least a cursory presence on IRC.

How am I, as someone working on a different project, supposed to reach out and have a discussion if the human does not exist on IRC?'}, {'account_id': 2472, 'date': '2018-08-08 13:37:00.000000000', 'content': 'Topic set to code-change'}, {'account_id': 2472, 'date': '2018-08-08 13:37:35.000000000', 'content': 'Topic changed from code-change to formal-vote'}, {'account_id': 5263, 'date': '2018-08-08 16:20:15.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

Monty Taylor wrote:

> I don't understand the assertion "at some level it's optional".
[...]

This is more about making sure that the site generation tooling doesn't fall over if there's no IRC nick supplied so that we don't hold off affirming PTLs who didn't supply their nicks to the election officials. I'm not strongly in favor or objecting, and ultimately I do think we need to solicit updates from these individuals to add them post-hoc.

I'd also be in favor of resolving to require them in future elections, which would then give the election officials license to reject candidacies until an IRC nick is supplied. The election officials simply didn't want to be in a position of seeming to overstep their bounds and implement policy of their own making, nor significantly alter the tooling in use in the midst of nomination week.'}, {'account_id': 2472, 'date': '2018-08-08 17:20:47.000000000', 'content': 'Topic changed from formal-vote to code-change'}, {'account_id': 2472, 'date': '2018-08-08 17:23:46.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Rollcall-Vote+1

> Monty Taylor wrote:
 > 
 > > I don't understand the assertion "at some level it's optional".
 > [...]
 > 
 > This is more about making sure that the site generation tooling
 > doesn't fall over if there's no IRC nick supplied so that we don't
 > hold off affirming PTLs who didn't supply their nicks to the
 > election officials. I'm not strongly in favor or objecting, and
 > ultimately I do think we need to solicit updates from these
 > individuals to add them post-hoc.
 > 
 > I'd also be in favor of resolving to require them in future
 > elections, which would then give the election officials license to
 > reject candidacies until an IRC nick is supplied. The election
 > officials simply didn't want to be in a position of seeming to
 > overstep their bounds and implement policy of their own making, nor
 > significantly alter the tooling in use in the midst of nomination
 > week.

Yes, let's formalize the rules for the contact information we expect a PTL to provide and track down information for the folks who have it missing.

In the mean time, I'm OK with moving ahead with this change.'}, {'account_id': 1004, 'date': '2018-08-08 17:26:16.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Rollcall-Vote+1

+1 to the technical limitations, +2 to resolving this requirement (but maybe we need to make sure all existing PTLs have an IRC presence)'}, {'account_id': 308, 'date': '2018-08-09 14:40:50.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

We should probably require that the nomination txt provides a IRC nick.'}, {'account_id': 5263, 'date': '2018-08-09 16:27:15.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

Thierry Carrez wrote:

> We should probably require that the nomination txt provides a IRC
> nick.

It would be nice, but the nomination text is currently entirely freeform specifically because it's already hard enough for candidates to follow directions that getting them to format the content of that file in a particular way (say, valid YAML or whatever) would mean that much more hand-holding from the officials.

As a compromise, they can put their IRC nick in their OSF member profile and our tooling can find it there automatically since it already needs to hit that API to check whether they're a foundation member in good standing."}, {'account_id': 8482, 'date': '2018-08-10 07:39:34.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

I prefer Zane's suggestion on https://review.openstack.org/#/c/589691/ to just change the wording of the placeholder so it's very clear that there is no known IRC contact."}, {'account_id': 12898, 'date': '2018-08-15 04:44:21.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

I'm not sure what to do with this.  It seems like we're willing to require a PTL to have an IRC presence and the way to supply that information is either via the OSF directory or with manual updates to projects.yaml.

With that in mind I'm happy to abandon this."}, {'account_id': 6088, 'date': '2018-08-17 10:47:31.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

So, while it is nice when PTLs are on IRC, we have never required it except by social means (and probably shouldn't start now).  For the pike, queens, and rocky cycles, the election process required the entry of an IRC nick to be nominated for PTL, but such nicks were not necessarily registered or maintained with persistent presence on IRC.  No effort was taken to ensure that the nick provided was used by the individual elected, nor that the person in question used IRC in any way.

If it is decided not to approve this change, then *other means* must be taken to ensure that IRC is a functional contact mechanism for PTLs.  A string in a YAML file, unbacked by explicit policy, is insufficient to assure that a PTL may be contactable via IRC when it happens to be convenient for whoever looked up the value in projects.yaml.

If it is decided to approve this change, the same mechanisms that are necessary to make the string meaningful could be used if there is consensus that maintaining consistent (if not persistent) presence on IRC is expected of PTLs."}, {'account_id': 4257, 'date': '2018-08-22 19:10:14.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

This seem unnecessary to me in light of Icd9ee24cb882e999ca92ab4eca4a8db12b0d83eb'}, {'account_id': 12898, 'date': '2018-08-23 00:10:06.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned'}]

commit_message:
Allow PTLs to not have an IRCnick

Wheil IRC is highly desired at some level it's optional so remove
placeholder 'None supplied' entries and allow the docs builder to omit
the ircnick if it isn't supplied.

Change-Id: I140dd96d03d861e2921542bdc4bba9fc8f89ad48

revisions:
[{'created': '2018-07-09 19:27:26.000000000', 'message': 'Rename "Member" role in tempest_roles to "member"

Recently, Keystone renamed "Member" role to "member"
(case-sensitive) with https://review.openstack.org/#/c/572243/14

Case-sensitivity role requirement in Keystone was recently
formalized with https://review.openstack.org/#/c/576640/

From the above reference:

"Role names are case-insensitive. for example, when keystone
bootstraps default roles, it creates `admin`, `member`, and
`reader`. If another role `Member` (note the upper case 'M') is
created, keystone will return a `409` Conflict since it considers
the name "Member" == "member". Note that case is preserved in these
cases."

It follows that Tempest should use "member" role by default.

Change-Id: Iebf04fdb4c195b6779c74f66da3f7822cf174494

commit_message:
Rename "Member" role in tempest_roles to "member"

Recently, Keystone renamed "Member" role to "member"
(case-sensitive) with https://review.openstack.org/#/c/572243/14

Case-sensitivity role requirement in Keystone was recently
formalized with https://review.openstack.org/#/c/576640/

From the above reference:

"Role names are case-insensitive. for example, when keystone
bootstraps default roles, it creates `admin`, `member`, and
`reader`. If another role `Member` (note the upper case 'M') is
created, keystone will return a `409` Conflict since it considers
the name "Member" == "member". Note that case is preserved in these
cases."

It follows that Tempest should use "member" role by default.

Change-Id: Iebf04fdb4c195b6779c74f66da3f7822cf174494

commit_message:
add a flag to filter patch lists to the imports

We only block the project-config cleanup patch as long as there are
import patches for a team. This makes it easier to determine that.

Change-Id: I7dbffe87ded1e9b79f0adcc94022722e689e2b2a
Signed-off-by: Doug Hellmann <doug@doughellmann.com>

commit_message:
Optimizing code (wrap_socket())

Since Python 3.2 and 2.7.9, it is recommended
to use the SSLContext.wrap_socket() instead of
wrap_socket().
The top-level function is limited and creates an
insecure client socket without server name
indication or hostname matching.

Ref : https://docs.python.org/3/library/ssl.html#ssl.wrap_socket

commit_message:
Remove ChanceScheduler

ChanceScheduler is deprecated in Pike [1] and will be removed in a
subsequent release.

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/492210/

Change-Id: I44f9c1cabf9fc64b1a6903236bc88f5ed8619e9e

commit_message:
Filter out instances without a host when populating AZ

It could happen that instance does not have a host set, e.g.
when its creation failed before it was scheduled.
During online_migration, populate_missing_availability_zones tries to
add missing AZs to all instances. However for instances without a host
there's no reasonable value for AZ (we can't use a logic that bases
the value on a host) so let's skip this kind of instances completely.

Change-Id: Ic6060beaa08af5ea70e5e54fffb94eea58aa7bbf
Closes-Bug: #1788115

commit_message:
Update python-senlinclient to use current openstacksdk

senlinclient still uses Profile, which is deprecated and marked for
removal. Update create_connection to be able to work in a post-Profile
world. Amongst other things, this was causing nothing to set the
default_microversion setting.

Also, make_client was calling create_connection, but it doesn't need to
because openstackclient already has an sdk_connection object that can be
used. Just return it.

Related to https://storyboard.openstack.org/#!/story/2003146

Change-Id: I7bc0bfdecf1b1461714de1da8b56e3e47154726d

to not be a private method.

commit_message:
get_subnet_for_dvr returns SNAT mac instead of distributed gateway in subnet_info

On hosts with dvr_snat agent mode, after restarting OVS agent,
sometimes the SNAT port is processed first instead of the distributed port.
The subnet_info is cached locally via get_subnet_for_dvr when either of these ports
are processed. However, it returns the MAC address of the port used to query
as the gateway for the subnet. Using the SNAT port, this puts the wrong
MAC as the gateway, causing some flows such as the DVR flows on br-int
for local src VMs to have the wrong MAC.

This patch fixes the get_subnet_for_dvr with fixed_ips as None for the csnat port,
as that causes the server side handler to fill in the subnet's actual gateway
rather than using the port's MAC.

Change-Id: If045851819fd53c3b9a1506cc52bc1757e6d6851
Closes-Bug: #1783470
(cherry picked from commit c6de172e58ed4cbd157c2e560ffbbb4dc3a34730)

commit_message:
Trivial: avoid KeyError while processing ports

The Neutron OVS agent logs can get flooded with KeyErrors as the
'_get_port_info' method skips the added/removed dict items if no
ports have been added/removed, which are expected to be present,
even if those are just empty sets.

This change ensures that those port info dict fields are always set.

Closes-Bug: #1783556

Change-Id: I9e5325aa2d8525231353ba451e8ea895be51b1ca
(cherry picked from commit da5b13df2b2a8171f60311414250671820390738)

commit_message:
Update UPPER_CONSTRAINTS_FILE for stable/rocky

The new stable upper-constraints file is only available
after the openstack/requirements repository is branched.
This will happen around the RC1 timeframe.

Recheck and merge this change once the requirements
repository has been branched.

The CI system will work with this patch before the requirements
repository is branched because zuul configues the job to run
with a local copy of the file and defaults to the master branch.
However, accepting the patch will break the test configuration
on developers' local systems, so please wait until after the
requirements repository is branched to merge the patch.

Change-Id: I31ce0ab289d40ac12007476aec2c7492c6e4be0f

commit_message:
Fix HASH for periodic jobs(use tripleo-ci-testing)

Periodic jobs should use 'tripleo-ci-testing' hash as
a target hash, currently 'current-tripleo' was used,
this patch fixes it.
Also added unit tests for the same.

Also allow using promotion-testing-hash-$release in
upgrade job in promotion pipeline.

Closes-Bug: #1787817
Change-Id: I8893c7406fcf1bb3936f5ba2d9dca7d4a3e9e82a

commit_message:
Update UPPER_CONSTRAINTS_FILE for stable/rocky

The new stable upper-constraints file is only available
after the openstack/requirements repository is branched.
This will happen around the RC1 timeframe.

Recheck and merge this change once the requirements
repository has been branched.

The CI system will work with this patch before the requirements
repository is branched because zuul configues the job to run
with a local copy of the file and defaults to the master branch.
However, accepting the patch will break the test configuration
on developers' local systems, so please wait until after the
requirements repository is branched to merge the patch.

Change-Id: I6b0607a839c4402b9a018ac7d4833265fd266d02

Doing this to fix the beaker issues with puppet-keystone https://review.openstack.org/#/c/593786/ which is because the python-chardet dependency is not updated, will be fixed by https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1620221

commit_message:
Always update packages after repos are added

This moves the current upgrade logic for RedHat based
in run_tests.sh to the repos manifest. This is
to make sure we run the upgrade phase in the beaker
tests as well otherwise the testing for these two will
differ.

Change-Id: Ia7964b73f525c9875ae7ba6e2388ed4c31e8b179

commit_message:
Open tarball in binary mode

Under python3 this open call fails in swiftclient because it tries to
decode the data using utf-8. Since we're uploading a binary tarball
anyway we should us binary i/o instead.

Change-Id: I5b8aff53e44024e916b9a491e52ffd9362ca39e4
Closes-Bug: #1788288

commit_message:
Use binary io for object saving

When interacting with the swiftclient under python3, we need to make
sure that we open files in binary mode so they aren't interpreted as
text when being read.

Change-Id: I9a7977c20850ad1e97bf8f536563832d3439625d
Closes-Bug: #1788307

revisions:
[{'created': '2018-07-31 13:32:53.000000000', 'message': "Allow custom UC/standalone passwords

Add --disable-password-generation /
undercloud_disable_password_generation to control passwords generation
for containerized UC and standalone installations. This allows users
to provide custom passwords/secrets in tripleo-undercloud-passwords.yaml.

Only consume instack legacy passwords when upgrading from instack, in
order to maintain upgrade idempotency and keep old passwords.
This also overrides passwords defined by users via tht
params in tripleo-undercloud-passwords.yaml, if any conflicts.

Ignore legacy instack passwords in undercloud-passwords.conf, if not
upgrading UC. This gives the preference to the users' custom passwords
defined in tripleo-undercloud-passwords.yaml (if any).

Always add DefaultPasswords, if unset by users or password generators.

Partial-bug: #1784576

Change-Id: If7166c2419794dd9595d25ad29ee1fdafce99d72
Signed-off-by: Bogdan Dobrelya <bdobreli@redhat.com>

commit_message:
Allow custom UC/standalone passwords

Fix the passwords generation precedence for containerized UC and
standalone installations. This allows users to provide custom
passwords/secrets in tripleo-undercloud-passwords.yaml, or
undercloud-passwords.conf, when upgrading from instack.

Partial-bug: #1784576

Change-Id: If7166c2419794dd9595d25ad29ee1fdafce99d72
Signed-off-by: Bogdan Dobrelya <bdobreli@redhat.com>

commit_message:
import zuul job settings from project-config

This is a mechanically generated patch to complete step 1 of moving
the zuul job settings out of project-config and into each project
repository.

Because there will be a separate patch on each branch, the branch
specifiers for branch-specific jobs have been removed.

Because this patch is generated by a script, there may be some
cosmetic changes to the layout of the YAML file(s) as the contents are
normalized.

See the python3-first goal document for details:
https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/stein/python3-first.html

Change-Id: I432d4f9f9e24396b9adce011e59cd58e016701d9
Story: #2002586
Task: #24324

(1 comment)

> Can you point me to the discussion that led to the desire to have
 > stable uuids. Not debating its validity, just curious about the
 > process.

I think a bit of it can be found in the neutron spec and its comments, but let me summarize here:

Originally we thought of using the UUID of the neutron agent (as in openstack network agent list) also for the agent RP UUID. However the agent UUID may change (it's rare though, eg. after openstack network agent delete and re-create). As soon as we have allocations on some of the RPs we can't just delete and re-create the RPs. We would need to re-parent RPs. That we wanted to avoid.

It also helps to keep the communication needs low if both a neutron agent and the server is able to deterministically generate RP UUIDs from inputs they already have (via v5 UUIDs). For example if neutron-server had generated an RP UUID we could have needed a new message to send it back to the agent too."}, {'account_id': 8313, 'date': '2018-08-06 12:45:38.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 9: Code-Review-1

Placement: utils

* to generate Placement trait names,
* to generate Placement resource provider UUIDs, and
* to uniformly parse and validate Placement-related config options in
  all agents.

Partial-Bug: #1578989

commit_message:
Add missing service for DockerCinderVolumeImage

OS::TripleO::Services::BlockStorageCinderVolume has a mandatory
DockerCinderVolumeImage parameter, but is missing an entry here, this
change adds that entry.

Change-Id: Ib818df1e2bcde3aa1713ad10b9aecc97d1b4eff8
Related-Bug: #1783653

commit_message:
Placement: constants

Introduce a constants file for later use for symbols in Placement,
including constants for:

* custom trait prefixes
* resource class names (though that should be replaced as soon as we
  have an os-resource-classes package)
* known inventory parameters to validate config options

Change-Id: I3a5afd04ce8b5919efdb7591e3717742dd27151e
Partial-Bug: #1578989
See-Also: https://review.openstack.org/502306 (nova spec)
See-Also: https://review.openstack.org/508149 (neutron spec)

Placement client: move to neutron_lib.placement

Move neutron_lib.clients.placement to neutron_lib.placement.client
with the intent of consolidating all Placement code under
neutron_lib.placement.

commit_message:
Fix no packet log data when debug is set False in configuration

In production environment, it's quite difficult to require operator
to enable debug log level. This patch changes LOG.debug to LOG.info
of packet_in_handler function. Therefore operator can get packet log
data while debug=False or True in config file. This patch also adds
timestamp to log_file if local_output_log_base is specified.

Closes-Bug #1781372
Change-Id: I729e57caecd502d018084c3c766278006bcbf0c9
(cherry picked from commit f937dd2a150f77f9c3de489acdafe2bdce13fdbe)

commit_message:
Update metering driver to load interface driver

Currently the metering iptables driver is using the old method
to load the interface driver. This patch allows it to load
interface driver via stevedore aliases.

Change-Id: I9e3027c1ec695ec3a09db0c53a0388e406e4ced6
Related-Bug: #1504536
(cherry picked from commit 38309ca4dc79e033a7b8384f4e9f1224c5a69524)

(1 comment)

Some comments on the commit message on why generations can't be fully removed.

What you've done here is the expected behavior when on the client side you don't care about generations.

In the instances where you don't care, but you might be a highly concurrent environment you might consider doing a retry when you get a 409: 

GET generation -> write inventory -> 409 from gen conflict -> start over (with GET generation)"}, {'account_id': 15554, 'date': '2018-07-31 13:46:57.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

(1 comment)

> In the instances where you don't care, but you might be a highly concurrent environment you might consider doing a retry when you get a 409:

My working assumption is that updates to the same RP from Neutron (for RPs that Neutron is solely responsible for) should never be highly concurrent. (Because they are triggered by periodic agent heartbeat messages.) Therefore I'd prefer not suppressing any errors that may be invalidating this assumption by automatic retries at the moment."}, {'account_id': 15554, 'date': '2018-08-01 10:53:10.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 4: Patch Set 3 was rebased.'}, {'account_id': 27654, 'date': '2018-08-07 21:16:40.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: Code-Review+1'}, {'account_id': 15554, 'date': '2018-08-09 08:13:19.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 5: Patch Set 4 was rebased.'}, {'account_id': 13995, 'date': '2018-08-14 20:58:36.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 5: Code-Review+1'}, {'account_id': 15554, 'date': '2018-08-15 09:42:51.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 6: Patch Set 5 was rebased.'}, {'account_id': 5367, 'date': '2018-08-15 14:30:14.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 6:

[{'created': '2018-07-06 14:05:55.000000000', 'message': 'WIP Placement client: optional RP generations

Make resource provider generation handling optional for trait and
inventory reporting. So the user of the client may choose to ignore
generations (single placement user in always override mode). And by that
remain I/O side effect free.

TODO tests

Change-Id: I4312c3f8819f7c5b74b68f6fa0507e42094eab79
Partial-Bug: #1578989
See-Also: https://review.openstack.org/502306 (nova spec)
See-Also: https://review.openstack.org/508149 (neutron spec)
'}, {'created': '2018-07-09 09:29:58.000000000', 'message': "Placement client: optional RP generations

The Placement API has the concept of resource provider generations to
enable the co-ordination of multiple API clients, so they can avoid
accidentally overwriting each other's updates.

However when we know that a single client writes certain resource
providers then the generation handling becomes an unrequited extra
API turnaround. Ideally the Placement API would give us a chance to
express our ignorance about multi-client coordination (accepting that
a single client can overwrite its own previous updates).

Until the Placement API gives us such a feature we implement it in
the client lib, by making 'resource_provider_generation' parameters
optional.  This is inferior to the API doing the same because we may
still see GenerationConflict exceptions even when we said
method(..., resource_provider_generation=None).

Later changes for the minimum guaranteed bandwidth
feature need 'resource_provider_generation' to be
optional for 'update_resource_provider_traits' and
'update_resource_provider_inventories'. For the sake of consistency
we do the same to 'update_resource_provider_inventory'.

Change-Id: I4312c3f8819f7c5b74b68f6fa0507e42094eab79
Partial-Bug: #1578989
See-Also: https://review.openstack.org/502306 (nova spec)
See-Also: https://review.openstack.org/508149 (neutron spec)

commit_message:
Placement client: optional RP generations

The Placement API has the concept of resource provider generations to
enable the co-ordination of multiple API clients, so they can avoid
accidentally overwriting each other's updates.

However when we know that a single client writes certain resource
providers then the generation handling becomes an unnecessary extra
API round-trip. Ideally the Placement API would give us a chance to
express our ignorance about multi-client coordination (accepting that
a single client can overwrite its own previous updates).

Until the Placement API gives us such a feature we implement it in
the client lib, by making 'resource_provider_generation' parameters
optional.  This is inferior to the API doing the same because we may
still see GenerationConflict exceptions even when we said
method(..., resource_provider_generation=None).

Later changes for the minimum guaranteed bandwidth
feature need 'resource_provider_generation' to be
optional for 'update_resource_provider_traits' and
'update_resource_provider_inventories'. For the sake of consistency
we do the same to 'update_resource_provider_inventory'.

Change-Id: I4312c3f8819f7c5b74b68f6fa0507e42094eab79
Partial-Bug: #1578989
See-Also: https://review.openstack.org/502306 (nova spec)
See-Also: https://review.openstack.org/508149 (neutron spec)

commit_message:
Placement client: ensure_resource_provider

All other API resources (ie. traits, resource_provider_traits and
resource_provider_inventories) we need to report on for minimum
guaranteed bandwidth have update methods that can be called in one go,
either because they have update-or-create or update-overrides-all
semantics. Here we add the 'ensure_resource_provider' method so
resource providers also have a similarly simple way of being kept in
sync.  We also add 'update_resource_provider' as a pre-requisite. On
the side we also fix a little, silent unit test type error.

Change-Id: Ib615ceeb323970d179ffb3dee14e52cb40e73ae7
Partial-Bug: #1578989
See-Also: https://review.openstack.org/502306 (nova spec)
See-Also: https://review.openstack.org/508149 (neutron spec)

commit_message:
Placement client: always return body

In a few POST and PUT calls we didn't return the JSON body of the
response we got. By that we were just throwing away information we
already waited for.

This patch makes sure that if the HTTP response had a body we return it.

We leave one exception: PUT /resource_classes/ microversions 1.2 - 1.6.
Usage of that is strongly discouraged and starting from 1.7 the response
no longer has a body.

Change-Id: Ifa4db6edd4c656023039f7a68c09bf2cea508231

[{'created': '2018-07-31 15:24:07.000000000', 'message': 'Handle binding_failed vif plug errors on compute restart

Like change Ia584dba66affb86787e3069df19bd17b89cb5c49 which
came before, is port binding fails and we have a "binding_failed"
vif type in the info cache, we'll fail to plug vifs for an
instance on compute restart which will prevent the service
from restarting. Before the os-vif conversion code, this was
handled with VirtualInterfacePlugException but the os-vif conversion
code fails in a different way, so this change adds a specific
exception type for that os-vif type conversion failure and handles
it in the same place (and way) in _init_instance.

Admittedly this isn't the smartest thing and doesn't attempt
to recover / fix the instance networking info, but it at least
gives a more clear indication of what's wrong and lets the
nova-compute service start up.

Change-Id: Ia963a093a1b26d90b4de2e8fc623031cf175aece
Closes-Bug: #1784579

commit_message:
Handle binding_failed vif plug errors on compute restart

Like change Ia584dba66affb86787e3069df19bd17b89cb5c49 which
came before, is port binding fails and we have a "binding_failed"
vif type in the info cache, we'll fail to plug vifs for an
instance on compute restart which will prevent the service
from restarting. Before the os-vif conversion code, this was
handled with VirtualInterfacePlugException but the os-vif conversion
code fails in a different way by raising a generic NovaException
because the os-vif conversion utility doesn't handle a vif_type of
"binding_failed".

To resolve this and make the os-vif flow for binding_failed behave
the same as the legacy path, we implement a translation function
in os_vif_util for binding_failed which will make the plug_vifs
code raise VirtualInterfacePlugException which is what the
_init_instance code in ComputeManager is already handling.

Admittedly this isn't the smartest thing and doesn't attempt
to recover / fix the instance networking info, but it at least
gives a more clear indication of what's wrong and lets the
nova-compute service start up. A note is left in the
_init_instance error handling that we could potentially try
to heal binding_failed vifs in _heal_instance_info_cache, but
that would need to be done in a separate change since it's more
invasive.

Change-Id: Ia963a093a1b26d90b4de2e8fc623031cf175aece
Closes-Bug: #1784579

commit_message:
Fix lost connection when create security group log

Packet sent to table 91 are considered accepted by the egress pipeline
and NORMAL action is used by default in this table. However, if we
create a security group logging resource, then ovs flows log will be
added into this table with higher priority. Therefore packet matches
with ovs flows log will be sent to CONTROLLER and never forward.
So this patch append action=NORMAL into ovs flows log to forward
the packet and send it to CONTROLLER for logging.

Closes-Bug: #1787106
Change-Id: I6e95e2e646ec8a5507c7f140ab2c4a56be8404c3
(cherry picked from commit 7d2ac2d0aff90d17d2e46aba2af3b4cc32d1833c)

commit_message:
update pylint to 1.9.2

The older version of pylint being used does not work
correctly under python 3. In order to be able to
update the pylint job to run under python 3,
we need to update the tool.

commit_message:
Update UPPER_CONSTRAINTS_FILE for stable/rocky

The new stable upper-constraints file is only available
after the openstack/requirements repository is branched.
This will happen around the RC1 timeframe.

Recheck and merge this change once the requirements
repository has been branched.

The CI system will work with this patch before the requirements
repository is branched because zuul configues the job to run
with a local copy of the file and defaults to the master branch.
However, accepting the patch will break the test configuration
on developers' local systems, so please wait until after the
requirements repository is branched to merge the patch.

Change-Id: Iccfe17c019ace476e81662cae1420d81637367cf

commit_message:
Deal with lack of neutron-plugin-openvswitch-agent

The neutron-plugin-openvswitch-agent package has been dropped @ Rocky.

Pre-install neutron-common and ensure any previously cached os_release
value is reset when evaluating which OpenStack release is being installed,
ensuring that the correct package for the neutron-openvswitch-agent is
used.

Closes-Bug: #1788266
Change-Id: I1224aa7f5e7caa6a8aaf2ab3043fac9c62735749

commit_message:
Update the segment api extension

The segment api definition is changed in server side [1]. This patch
sync up the definition in neutron-lib. In addition, remove the
dependency from standard-attr-segment on segment since the
dependency is reserved: we have segment depending on
standard-attr-segment with the latest change.

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/571292/

Change-Id: I64780fc435da98d9b5d4e58c9e61d3d0b11d0daf

commit_message:
Update UPPER_CONSTRAINTS_FILE for stable/rocky

The new stable upper-constraints file is only available
after the openstack/requirements repository is branched.
This will happen around the RC1 timeframe.

Recheck and merge this change once the requirements
repository has been branched.

The CI system will work with this patch before the requirements
repository is branched because zuul configues the job to run
with a local copy of the file and defaults to the master branch.
However, accepting the patch will break the test configuration
on developers' local systems, so please wait until after the
requirements repository is branched to merge the patch.

Change-Id: Id2c26aac9c39e413c455a8aeb50e8fe853428f35

commit_message:
Upgrades: Refactor playbooks to set facts

To not to redefine variable multiple times in each service we
run check only once and we set fact. To increase readability of
generated playbook we add block per strep in services.

Partial-Bug: #1785028

(cherry picked from commit 56bec75c02b56bab79f35bc94c9110ee93eab82f)

messages: [{'account_id': 17591, 'date': '2018-08-20 16:03:00.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 1.'}, {'account_id': 23928, 'date': '2018-08-20 17:37:11.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review+2'}, {'account_id': 7769, 'date': '2018-08-22 15:25:33.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review+2 Workflow+1'}]
revisions:
[{'created': '2018-08-20 16:03:00.000000000', 'message': 'Grafana: Update default refresh intervals, enable gate ingress

This updates the grafana dashboards to use a default refresh
value of 5m to prevent dashboards with intensive queries (like the
container dashboard) from submitting frequent, expensive requests
to Prometheus

This also removes the override to disable the ingress service for
grafana in the developer deployment script, as it was overlooked
when enabling ingresses after the ingress chart was introduced

Change-Id: I0958a3978cec25a1350172cbe75996f1346858c5
'}]
commit_message:
Grafana: Update default refresh intervals, enable gate ingress

This updates the grafana dashboards to use a default refresh
value of 5m to prevent dashboards with intensive queries (like the
container dashboard) from submitting frequent, expensive requests
to Prometheus

This also removes the override to disable the ingress service for
grafana in the developer deployment script, as it was overlooked
when enabling ingresses after the ingress chart was introduced

Change-Id: I0958a3978cec25a1350172cbe75996f1346858c5

commit_message:
Prometheus: Remove block duration flags, update cadvisor job

This removes the min_block_duration and max_block_duration flags
from the Prometheus chart, as the suggested best practice is to
use the defaults (2h min, 10% of retention time as max).

This also updates the scrape target configuration for cadvisor to
match the upstream example endpoint for kubernetes versions 1.7.3
and later

Change-Id: I200969d6c4da9d17d0a7d3a34a114ccc5f5ee70f

commit_message:
Fluentd: Change default image

This updates Fluentd to use the stable v1.2 debian fluentd
image instead of the kolla image. This images comes bundled
with the elasticsearch plugin, and provides more
flexibility in configuring the buffer behavior of the output
plugins

Change-Id: Id446ef1e050f5d9c005c94dae661cf9ae88fffea

commit_message:
Fluentd: Filter out fluentd's logs

This filters out fluentd's logs for collection, as this can result
in infinite loops as fluentd will try to process the events in its
own logs repeatedly

Change-Id: I85cce909b6917901b964cb5cc479403143c4d211

commit_message:
Make solidfire code py3-compatible

The solidfire volume driver was using dict.iteritems, which has been
removed in python 3 [1]. This replaces that usage with dict.items,
which also works in python 2.7, as recommended.

[1] https://wiki.python.org/moin/Python3.0#Built-In_Changes

Change-Id: I905cb8ec9dbfb2e66de6e14eb3263e8245791e49

commit_message:
Add mks_console option to compute-feature-enabled

Since microversion 2.8 creating a remote console works
with the mks protocol [0] so this is to add the relevant
option to Tempest's conf. This is consistent with Tempest
offering an option for each of the other console protocols
like rdp, serial, spice, and vnc.

[0] https://docs.openstack.org/nova/latest/reference/api-microversion-history.html#id7

Change-Id: Icb27984fb70521a166e9e5022997da90e768577b

commit_message:
import zuul job settings from project-config

This is a mechanically generated patch to complete step 1 of moving
the zuul job settings out of project-config and into each project
repository.

Because there will be a separate patch on each branch, the branch
specifiers for branch-specific jobs have been removed.

Because this patch is generated by a script, there may be some
cosmetic changes to the layout of the YAML file(s) as the contents are
normalized.

See the python3-first goal document for details:
https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/stein/python3-first.html

Change-Id: I486e6f8c69aece65ba9b0272004b88ea30c343cb
Story: #2002586
Task: #24321

Running agents on all nodes.

Using a node selector can not run the fluent-bit or node-exporter
on the master node. So, This PS changes the scheduling to use
either taint/toleration or the node selector.

Change-Id: I0ca80a6e645b7047469288697387f0f5bf111345

commit_message:
Install neutron-common early for OS release determination

Install neutron-common early to allow os_release to determine the
correct release. This charm is a subordinate charm and therefore
can't determine the release based on openstack-origin. Without this
change, os_release will always use the default release in the
install hook.

Change-Id: I751bf6ba3e9e299fc57bc623c96cfead94532092
Closes-Bug: #1788266

commit_message:
Remove user_group option

In Pike[1], we introduced a user_group auto detection for haproxy.
The default user group name is auto-detected for any OS distribution
we support as a base for Amphorae.

user_group remained as an option for admins but was also
marked deprecated in Pike[2].

This patch removes that option altogether.

Story: 2003323
Task: 24357

[1] Ia8fede9d7da4709a48661d1fc595a16d04fcbfa9
[2] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/429398/45/octavia/common/config.py@175

Change-Id: Iddd4162674f116705d2b47062cbf7ca88f2677a6
(cherry picked from commit 100858fa792fd621a134151e78a3f9001fcba3f0)

subject: Increase timeout from 180 mins to 200 mins
revisions:
[{'created': '2018-08-22 08:16:05.000000000', 'message': 'Increase timeout from 180 mins to 200 mins

Increase timeout from 180 mins to 200 mins fter observing that 14% of
jobs failed as timeout and others failed in post due to same issue.
This happened with any jobs but a most of them were update ones which
are known to be longer.

At least one update job has an avergage success duration of 10013 secs
which is too close to the cutout. This generated extra failures and
total estimated failure rate due to timeout went ~20%. This translates
to a huge extra load on CI because the only thing a developer would
do is to do a recheck.

Without having a ~10% safety net spare build time, we would would
endup prevent almost any change from going in.

Change-Id: I7dff9ae1afe9901fbfdc6096b607668f3f9aec79
'}]
commit_message:
Increase timeout from 180 mins to 200 mins

Increase timeout from 180 mins to 200 mins fter observing that 14% of
jobs failed as timeout and others failed in post due to same issue.
This happened with any jobs but a most of them were update ones which
are known to be longer.

At least one update job has an avergage success duration of 10013 secs
which is too close to the cutout. This generated extra failures and
total estimated failure rate due to timeout went ~20%. This translates
to a huge extra load on CI because the only thing a developer would
do is to do a recheck.

Without having a ~10% safety net spare build time, we would would
endup prevent almost any change from going in.

Change-Id: I7dff9ae1afe9901fbfdc6096b607668f3f9aec79

[{'created': '2018-02-15 16:40:20.000000000', 'message': 'Fix newton/ocata upgrade branching

In https://review.openstack.org/493057/ it was noticed that we
had made a mistake in a previous stable branch addition where
we missed setting stable/newton upgrading to stable/ocata. We
were going to follow up with a different patch to fix it, but
did not follow through until now.

This is really of limited use now since newton is EOL, but
making the change for now so it is at least right for any
trailing uses. It will likely just be removed completely
soon.

Change-Id: I4cd81390f8569311728d0c69e087c399a0b3a0c3
'}]
commit_message:
Fix newton/ocata upgrade branching

In https://review.openstack.org/493057/ it was noticed that we
had made a mistake in a previous stable branch addition where
we missed setting stable/newton upgrading to stable/ocata. We
were going to follow up with a different patch to fix it, but
did not follow through until now.

This is really of limited use now since newton is EOL, but
making the change for now so it is at least right for any
trailing uses. It will likely just be removed completely
soon.

Change-Id: I4cd81390f8569311728d0c69e087c399a0b3a0c3

AIO: Tune the nova scheduler workers down

To optimise memory/cpu usage, we tune the number of
scheduler workers from the default of 8 down to 1.

Remove -u root as mysql is executed with root user

As openstack installation guides suggest to run mysql with root shell
user, mysql will not ask for password, so in
controller-install-*.rst "-u root -p" is useless.

Related-Bug: #1785025

commit_message:
Update UPPER_CONSTRAINTS_FILE for stable/rocky

The new stable upper-constraints file is only available
after the openstack/requirements repository is branched.
This will happen around the RC1 timeframe.

Recheck and merge this change once the requirements
repository has been branched.

The CI system will work with this patch before the requirements
repository is branched because zuul configues the job to run
with a local copy of the file and defaults to the master branch.
However, accepting the patch will break the test configuration
on developers' local systems, so please wait until after the
requirements repository is branched to merge the patch.

Change-Id: I623cd9b65afae23f74e777f8db75ca286c5111a3

commit_message:
Assert container's ssl cert exists before upgrade.

While performing upgrade from Q to R undercloud is switched
from non-containerized to containerized, so some kolla* specific
dirs/files might not exist.
This change adds asserts if that dirs exis before manipulating
them.

Change-Id: I0fe99cc5cd10c7f78798e31435058908d0184973

commit_message:
Fix bind-mount to manila's bootstrap container

When deploying with tls-everywhere, there are
more connection options necessary for the Overcloud
manila database bootstrap container to connect
to mysql. These connection options are present in
the configuration folder
/var/lib/config-data/manila/etc/my.cnf.d/tripleo.cnf.

Fix the bind-mounts on the manila_api_db_sync
container so it doesn't fail to find this
configuration.

Closes-Bug: #1788337
Change-Id: I44133b0b0c4367214649777680c94dcfa7bddc76

commit_message:
Don't wait for an event on a resize-revert

Since we never unplugged, the event ain't comin'.

Sadly, the test that covers this was pretty wrong on multiple fronts,
which this patch fixes up.

Closes-Bug: #1450624
Change-Id: Id515137747a4b76e9b7057c95f80c8ae74017519

commit_message:
undercloud: revert to using the iscsi deploy interface by default

The direct deploy interface looks promising in the scale tests so far,
but it prevent local testing and PoC with nodes with less than 8 GiB
RAM because it has to convert the overcloud-full image in memory.

This change changes back to the iscsi deploy interface, leaving
the direct deploy interface fully configured and opt-in.

This patch will likely be reverted in Stein.

Change-Id: I5f8126474ab15a310b4ba305c4d537b93e9f0399
Related-Blueprint: ironic-direct-deploy

commit_message:
Update UPPER_CONSTRAINTS_FILE for stable/rocky

The new stable upper-constraints file is only available
after the openstack/requirements repository is branched.
This will happen around the RC1 timeframe.

Recheck and merge this change once the requirements
repository has been branched.

The CI system will work with this patch before the requirements
repository is branched because zuul configues the job to run
with a local copy of the file and defaults to the master branch.
However, accepting the patch will break the test configuration
on developers' local systems, so please wait until after the
requirements repository is branched to merge the patch.

Change-Id: Ieecb09ee507b237215ef8340da98f55179f0584e

the zuul job settings out of project-config and into each project
repository.

Because there will be a separate patch on each branch, the branch
specifiers for branch-specific jobs have been removed.

Because this patch is generated by a script, there may be some
cosmetic changes to the layout of the YAML file(s) as the contents are
normalized.

See the python3-first goal document for details:

commit_message:
import zuul job settings from project-config

This is a mechanically generated patch to complete step 1 of moving
the zuul job settings out of project-config and into each project
repository.

Because there will be a separate patch on each branch, the branch
specifiers for branch-specific jobs have been removed.

Because this patch is generated by a script, there may be some
cosmetic changes to the layout of the YAML file(s) as the contents are
normalized.

See the python3-first goal document for details:
https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/stein/python3-first.html

Change-Id: I9fb0ba0a9b7f011460a6a9239ec14e86eff7ba74
Story: #2002586
Task: #24302

'}, {'created': '2018-07-24 10:27:30.000000000', 'message': 'Remove tripleo.sh --bootstrap-subnodes add ceph loop device

As part of srpint 16 we are trying to remove usage of the tripleo.sh
script in ci in particular the invocation of bootstrap-subnodes [1].

This was initially proposed as stand-alone role in [2] but discussion
has led us to keeping only creation of the ceph loop device, added
here as ansible tasks in a tripleo-ci/pre.yaml. This is included
in the pre-run for the tripleo-ci-base job (zuul-v3) and also
the legacy jobs.

Also removes any variables used with the bootstrap-subnodes like
BOOTSTRAP_SUBNODES_MINIMAL etc and any invocations of tripleo.sh
--bootstrap.. is removed.

commit_message:
Remove tripleo.sh --bootstrap-subnodes add ceph loop device

As part of sprint 16 we want to remove tripleo.sh usage from ci in
particular the invocation of bootstrap-subnodes [1].

This was initially proposed as stand-alone role in [2] but discussion
has led us to keeping only creation of the ceph loop device, added
here as ansible tasks in a tripleo-ci/ceph.yaml. This is included
in the pre-run for the tripleo-ci-base job (zuul-v3) but not for
legacy jobs. That needs to wait for [3] and related testing/other
changes.

This removes any calls to tripleo.sh --bootstrap-subnodes from the
templated .j2 version of toci_gate_test and common_functions and
adds the new tripleo-ci/ceph.yaml in pre-run of tripleo-ci-base

Non templated scripts can be changed in a followup after [3].

[1] https://trello.com/c/GvjcnJB2/850-translate-tripleosh-bootstrap-subnodes-into-a-series-of-tasks
[2] https://review.openstack.org/581026
[3] https://review.rdoproject.org/r/#/c/15000
Depends-On: Ib95b02767488aaddfe95633d03cb118dd492a700
Change-Id: I1616a41914ca7142bd7d936ff906c54249012bbb

commit_message:
Add networking-odl for periodic-stable jobs

This was left out from previous commit [1], so now both 'check' and
'gate' jobs work, but the periodic-stable jobs fail: networking-odl is
required for jobs on queens and older stable branches. From rocky,
there is no tox_install.sh any more, so this is not needed there.

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/572368/

commit_message:
Update UPPER_CONSTRAINTS_FILE for stable/rocky

The new stable upper-constraints file is only available
after the openstack/requirements repository is branched.
This will happen around the RC1 timeframe.

Recheck and merge this change once the requirements
repository has been branched.

The CI system will work with this patch before the requirements
repository is branched because zuul configues the job to run
with a local copy of the file and defaults to the master branch.
However, accepting the patch will break the test configuration
on developers' local systems, so please wait until after the
requirements repository is branched to merge the patch.

Change-Id: I0ed503205d6460cfd1d9ef3309d5756c3ce90738

subject: Add MooseFS/MooseFS Pro Volume Driver
messages: [{'account_id': 28389, 'date': '2018-08-22 12:41:52.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 1.'}, {'account_id': 28389, 'date': '2018-08-22 13:19:23.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned\n\nAmmend commit without changeid'}]
revisions:
[{'created': '2018-08-22 12:41:52.000000000', 'message': 'Add MooseFS/MooseFS Pro Volume Driver

Add a volume driver which can use MooseFS.
MooseFS is an Open-source, POSIX-compliant distributed file system.
MooseFS aims to be fault-tolerant, highly available, highly
performing, scalable general-purpose network distributed file system
for data centers.
Driver has very similiar workflow to NFS, SMBFS or Virtuozzo.

Partially-Implements: driver-for-moosefs

Depends-On: I16a0e6e4eeadc5ce3da439763261bb427cb1d438

commit_message:
Add MooseFS/MooseFS Pro Volume Driver

Add a volume driver which can use MooseFS.
MooseFS is an Open-source, POSIX-compliant distributed file system.
MooseFS aims to be fault-tolerant, highly available, highly
performing, scalable general-purpose network distributed file system
for data centers.
Driver has very similiar workflow to NFS, SMBFS or Virtuozzo.

Partially-Implements: driver-for-moosefs

Depends-On: I16a0e6e4eeadc5ce3da439763261bb427cb1d438
Change-Id: I10e38fef0a47e73f2651bb6221c011f603cc1e0e

commit_message:
Update api-ref for unified limits

This patch did:
1. Change the empty string "" to null for `description` property
2. Add the missing `project_id` property back.
3. Add `project_id` filter for listing limits
4. Add `include_limits` filter for showing project

Change-Id: Iffaec737739a29ff81e10f7db33abfc3181fdbbe

commit_message:
Update UPPER_CONSTRAINTS_FILE for stable/rocky

The new stable upper-constraints file is only available
after the openstack/requirements repository is branched.
This will happen around the RC1 timeframe.

Recheck and merge this change once the requirements
repository has been branched.

The CI system will work with this patch before the requirements
repository is branched because zuul configues the job to run
with a local copy of the file and defaults to the master branch.
However, accepting the patch will break the test configuration
on developers' local systems, so please wait until after the
requirements repository is branched to merge the patch.

Change-Id: Iaf697d87201867820629b4e1f1bc7ebf7269f0f2

commit_message:
RemoteFS: Use summarize option for "du"

Only return the total from du rather than
a full listing.

The parsing code here expects du's output to
only be one line.

Closes-Bug: #1781276

Change-Id: Id398ad1ce3f30ccc029bfcfb1663654946d42c91
(cherry picked from commit 48a61877cee8665c96a16025e33b693636e9a359)

subject: Small prettification of README
messages:
[{'account_id': 28899, 'date': '2018-08-13 11:28:41.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 1.'}, {'account_id': 10068, 'date': '2018-08-13 11:28:51.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

Thank you for your first contribution to OpenStack.

    Your patch will now be tested automatically by OpenStack testing frameworks
    and once the automatic tests pass, it will be reviewed by other friendly
    developers. They will give you feedback and may require you to refine it.

    People seldom get their patch approved on the first try, so don't be
    concerned if requested to make corrections. Feel free to modify your patch
    and resubmit a new change-set.

    Patches usually take 3 to 7 days to be reviewed so be patient and be
    available on IRC to ask and answer questions about your work. Also it
    takes generally at least a couple of weeks for cores to get around to
    reviewing code. The more you participate in the community the more
    rewarding it is for you. You may also notice that the more you get to know
    people and get to be known, the faster your patches will be reviewed and
    eventually approved. Get to know others and become known by doing code
    reviews: anybody can do it, and it's a great way to learn the code base.

    Thanks again for supporting OpenStack, we look forward to working with you.

    IRC: https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/IRC
    Workflow: http://docs.openstack.org/infra/manual/developers.html
    Commit Messages: https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/GitCommitMessages"}, {'account_id': 13686, 'date': '2018-08-13 12:46:27.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

(1 comment)

Thank you for your proposal Vladimir.

Unfortunately the lines you are proposing a change for is about to be removed, take a look at https://review.openstack.org/#/c/588220/

Other than that take a look at the in-line comment.'}, {'account_id': 28899, 'date': '2018-08-22 13:14:11.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned'}]

commit_message:
Update UPPER_CONSTRAINTS_FILE for stable/rocky

The new stable upper-constraints file is only available
after the openstack/requirements repository is branched.
This will happen around the RC1 timeframe.

Recheck and merge this change once the requirements
repository has been branched.

The CI system will work with this patch before the requirements
repository is branched because zuul configues the job to run
with a local copy of the file and defaults to the master branch.
However, accepting the patch will break the test configuration
on developers' local systems, so please wait until after the
requirements repository is branched to merge the patch.

Change-Id: Ib983dead60556d060e76bc554c92f049ea30102c

commit_message:
fix tox python3 overrides

We want to default to running all tox environments under python 3, so
set the basepython value in each environment.

We do not want to specify a minor version number, because we do not
want to have to update the file every time we upgrade python.

We do not want to set the override once in testenv, because that
breaks the more specific versions used in default environments like
py35 and py36.

Change-Id: I032c95bbd02b800aebced158fb3936cdfd0797f1

commit_message:
fix tox python3 overrides

We want to default to running all tox environments under python 3, so
set the basepython value in each environment.

We do not want to specify a minor version number, because we do not
want to have to update the file every time we upgrade python.

We do not want to set the override once in testenv, because that
breaks the more specific versions used in default environments like
py35 and py36.

Change-Id: I4e8f6aa908767eeff25a129bb5e012fc4f9462bf

commit_message:
Update UPPER_CONSTRAINTS_FILE for stable/rocky

The new stable upper-constraints file is only available
after the openstack/requirements repository is branched.
This will happen around the RC1 timeframe.

Recheck and merge this change once the requirements
repository has been branched.

The CI system will work with this patch before the requirements
repository is branched because zuul configues the job to run
with a local copy of the file and defaults to the master branch.
However, accepting the patch will break the test configuration
on developers' local systems, so please wait until after the
requirements repository is branched to merge the patch.

Change-Id: Id7411e527519a26c290d65bbfc952e1786a83723

[{'created': '2018-08-10 13:00:50.000000000', 'message': "Adding a v2 storage backend

This adds a v2 storage interface as well as a gnocchi backend for it to
cloudkitty. This new interface will allow us to implement the v2 API, which will
be more metric-oriented.

This new storage uses the new dataframe format ('desc' is now split up into
'groupby' and 'metadata', following the collect logic); and supports grouping,
filters and pagination.

Modifications:

  * The tenant/scope state management isn't handled by the storage backend
    anymore. A StateManager object has been added.

  * All internal interactions with the storage backend use the v2 interface.
    An adapter class has been added to ensure retrocompatibility with the
    v1 interface.

  * A base class for functional tests testing the v2 storage interface has been
    added. It contains generic tests, which should allow easier testing for new
    v2 backends.

  * Some developer documentation explaining how to implement a v2 storage
    backend has been added. User documentation will be updated once the v2
    storage backend is considered stable.

The v1 is still the default storage version. Note that this new version is
considered unstable and should only be used for upstream development.

Change-Id: I5e9b95c79292582fab3017289d35ee310e35ffea
Story: 2001372

commit_message:
Adding a v2 storage backend

This adds a v2 storage interface as well as a gnocchi backend for it to
cloudkitty. This new interface will allow us to implement the v2 API, which will
be more metric-oriented.

This new storage uses the new dataframe format ('desc' is now split up into
'groupby' and 'metadata', following the collect logic); and supports grouping,
filters and pagination.

Modifications:

  * The tenant/scope state management isn't handled by the storage backend
    anymore. A StateManager object has been added.

  * All internal interactions with the storage backend use the v2 interface.
    An adapter class has been added to ensure retrocompatibility with the
    v1 interface.

  * A base class for functional tests testing the v2 storage interface has been
    added. It contains generic tests, which should allow easier testing for new
    v2 backends.

  * Some developer documentation explaining how to implement a v2 storage
    backend has been added. User documentation will be updated once the v2
    storage backend is considered stable.

The v1 is still the default storage version. Note that this new version is
considered unstable and should only be used for upstream development.

Change-Id: I5e9b95c79292582fab3017289d35ee310e35ffea

commit_message:
Allow the number of scheduler workers to be tuned

Similar to the other non-uwsgi services, the number of scheduler
workers can now be tuned [1]. We enable this to be used by adding
a tunable for it.

[1] https://review.openstack.org/159382

Change-Id: I523acc0e613d94278a1e3dbb403a08fe3b8549f5

commit_message:
Use monasca venv for influxdb setup

Instead of pip installing onto the host, we use the
influxdb in the monasca venv to do the influxdb database,
user, etc setup. This prevents interference between pip
installed packages and distribution packages, keeping the
line between host installed packages and venv installed
packages clean.

The venv is only deployed on the monasca_api servers, so
we change the group used for executing the tasks to the
right group for it to work.

Change-Id: I6e1f86a789f188dff611d522a3309a355f7cd8e8

commit_message:
Use the TESTING_BRANCH env var for constraints

The TESTING_BRANCH environment variable is provided by the
run_tests.sh script and is derived from the .gitreview file.

This ensures that once the master branch becomes a stable
branch, the constraints from the stable branch in the
integrated repository will automatically get used once the
.gitreview file is updated.

To ensure that the required environment variables are present
we export them appropriately in run_tests.sh and modify the
tox configuration to pass them into the tox test.

Change-Id: Ia785787095195017a22d9ffe5639edcf66434a55
Needed-By: https://review.openstack.org/579371

commit_message:
Update UPPER_CONSTRAINTS_FILE for stable/rocky

The new stable upper-constraints file is only available
after the openstack/requirements repository is branched.
This will happen around the RC1 timeframe.

Recheck and merge this change once the requirements
repository has been branched.

The CI system will work with this patch before the requirements
repository is branched because zuul configues the job to run
with a local copy of the file and defaults to the master branch.
However, accepting the patch will break the test configuration
on developers' local systems, so please wait until after the
requirements repository is branched to merge the patch.

Change-Id: I82e407b5e67498fea11550a41cb6613999f63efe

Update UPPER_CONSTRAINTS_FILE for stable/rocky

The new stable upper-constraints file is only available
after the openstack/requirements repository is branched.
This will happen around the RC1 timeframe.

Recheck and merge this change once the requirements
repository has been branched.

The CI system will work with this patch before the requirements
repository is branched because zuul configues the job to run
with a local copy of the file and defaults to the master branch.
However, accepting the patch will break the test configuration
on developers' local systems, so please wait until after the
requirements repository is branched to merge the patch.

[{'created': '2018-08-21 09:34:09.000000000', 'message': "Set quota for octavia service project

The default quotas are often not sufficient for a side wide
load balancing service. This will adjust them to some more
reasonable values.

The os_quota module of ansible assumes an installed
block storage service so it is not suitable for our
tests which don't install cinder. Therefore we
are using the openstack client straight.

Change-Id: If85cc3862b9316d9bf43e025bfaab8e1b7fd5576
(cherry picked from commit 3d0dfb706ca336351cc1f25a2afa55c665e02258)
"}]
commit_message:
Set quota for octavia service project

The default quotas are often not sufficient for a side wide
load balancing service. This will adjust them to some more
reasonable values.

The os_quota module of ansible assumes an installed
block storage service so it is not suitable for our
tests which don't install cinder. Therefore we
are using the openstack client straight.

Change-Id: If85cc3862b9316d9bf43e025bfaab8e1b7fd5576
(cherry picked from commit 3d0dfb706ca336351cc1f25a2afa55c665e02258)

commit_message:
Update openstack-tox-docs to follow build-sphinx better

The build-sphinx job uses compile and test bindep profiles, update
openstack-tox-docs to use the same.

openstack-tox-docs used to run tools/test_setup due to inheriting from unittests,
remove that inheritance since we do not need it, inherit from tox-docs
instead.

Change-Id: I74cb504c2ac6f2035f201ede2138e2af159555af
Depends-On: https://review.openstack.org/594802

commit_message:
import zuul job settings from project-config

This is a mechanically generated patch to complete step 1 of moving
the zuul job settings out of project-config and into each project
repository.

Because there will be a separate patch on each branch, the branch
specifiers for branch-specific jobs have been removed.

Because this patch is generated by a script, there may be some
cosmetic changes to the layout of the YAML file(s) as the contents are
normalized.

See the python3-first goal document for details:
https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/stein/python3-first.html

Change-Id: I92ff1b20ed7347e1adec3383244cf479249b767e
Story: #2002586
Task: #24321

[{'created': '2018-08-21 09:33:24.000000000', 'message': "Remove octavia_requires_pip_packages

commit_message:
Remove octavia_requires_pip_packages

In order to reduce the packages required to pip install on to the hosts,
we use service delegation to octavia_service_setup_host so that instead
of installing software on the target host, and putting credentials on
every target host, we isolate the software and credentials to a single
host.

In this patch we finally remove octavia_requires_pip_packages as it is
no longer required given that all services use delegation to the
octavia_service_setup_host now. We also remove the task which used to
install them.

We also remove the meta dependency on the openstack_openrc role because
the target host does not require openrc/clouds.yaml any more.

We remove the variable 'octavia_ansible_endpoint_type' as it is no longer
used.

We finally remove the python-pip package from the distro packages, as
with these changes, pip is no longer required on the host - everything
installed by pip is isolated into a venv.

Change-Id: If3f65fdb8a59a3c41cb8c2f0dee6b2e5a71f05c7
(cherry picked from commit 14d518607946ed1046d01f7cdff161c1e5aee883)

import zuul job settings from project-config

the zuul job settings out of project-config and into each project
repository.

commit_message:
Use print function rather than statement in tests

Python3 does not support the print statement, only the print function.
Whereas Python 2.6 and 2.7 support both.

Until statement is used, executing pylint via python3 on these files
causes error.

There is no more old way print in trove repository.

Change-Id: I063eb9dd7e690ac2cdc92810982c7f9a6ae22388
Signed-off-by: Marcin Piwowarczyk <m.piwowarczy@samsung.com>

commit_message:
Update openstack-tox-docs to follow build-sphinx better

The build-sphinx job uses compile and test bindep profiles,
update openstack-tox-docs to use the same.

was not run for build-sphinx.

commit_message:
nova: Configure console options in nova-cpu.conf

The options in the '[vnc]' and '[spice]' groups are only used by
'nova-compute' services. There's no need to store them in the global
'nova.conf' file and placing them here can lead to time wasted wondering
why configuration isn't being updated.

Change-Id: Iec0db477f391a063c5e52f9aed8a8dae0de15e54

commit_message:
Ensure resource_key is in groupby in Monasca collector

We could have added the 'resource_key' option to group_by, but it would have
forced a per_resource grouping (which we don't want) and would have been
opaque to users.

Documentation should be updated in order to explain this once #592329
is merged.

Change-Id: I39571095860ad71534f05e982f1fc5b45b842d09

commit_message:
Added Handling Newer Quobyte API Error Codes

This added the capability to expect specific error codes when doing a
RPC call in the Quobyte driver. This is used to handle the newer
API error codes in newer (1.4+) Quobyte API versions. This also adds
explicitely creating a Quobyte tenant.

Closes-Bug: #1733807

Change-Id: I65e87e6f50e12bfbe5d7a8fd988ca14bddd212da
(cherry picked from commit 269942101be6de85005969af6b700dbcfdccedd1)

commit_message:
Add Prometheus Collector

* Add Prometheus Collector that supports Prometheus HTTP instant queries.

* Due to the design of Cloudkitty, only instant queries are supported as
  the time window used by Prometheus can exceed the one used by Cloudkitty,
  using range queries, especially if coupled with function that
  makes calculation back in time from a supplied timestamp
  (e.g. increase(), delta()).

Change-Id: I4ba137b0b079f5ae6bfb645372778698eaa391fc

revisions:
[{'created': '2018-08-21 09:22:26.000000000', 'message': '[DNM] Remove bonds from AIO network config

On bionic the network bridges refuse to be up, because the underlying
bond interfaces do not come up.

This change removes the bonds which were really only decorative, and plugs

commit_message:
Remove bonds from AIO network config

On bionic the network bridges refuse to be up, because the underlying
bond interfaces do not come up.

This change removes the bonds which were really only decorative, and plugs
a dedicated dummy interface into each bridge. This simplifies the config
and the bridges should come up as soon as the dummy interface is attached.

Change-Id: I2662df94929c30190cd5d303588fdc9a99370e87

commit_message:
Ensure that tests fail early if network interfaces are down

Interfaces such as eth12 are required to be working for functional
tests such as healthcheck/tempest, and we waste a lot of CI time
when these interfaces do not come up properly during host preparation.

This change makes the build fail if either:

* The network bridges do not come up after creation
* The new interfaces eth12/13/14 are not up after host bootstrap

Change-Id: Idf83b48beab29e9044fbc0e6d4eacc89f68bf18f

commit_message:
[k8s] Add proxy to master and set cluster-cidr

1. pods with host network can not reach coredns or any svc or resolve
their own hostname
2. If webhooks are deployed in the cluster, the apiserver needs to
contact them, which means kube-proxy is required in the master node with
the cluster-cidr set.

Change-Id: Icb8e7c3b8c75a3ab087c818c8580c0c8a9111d30
story: 2003460
task: 24719
(cherry picked from commit 4f121e50c547abee195e30ce4aef588f71f509ee)

1. Remove tests/test-configure-octavia.yml because the 'shade' package
   does not need to be installed again - this is already done by the

2. Remove the key generation as the keys are already generated in the

3. Add some spacing between tasks to make it more readable.

4. Implement the extra packages needed in test-requirements.txt instead

commit_message:
Clean up tests a bit

1. Remove tests/test-configure-octavia.yml because the 'shade' package
   does not need to be installed again - this is already done by the
   role test preparation.

2. Remove the key generation as the keys are already generated in the
   common tests playbook 'test-prepare-keys.yml'.

3. Add some spacing between tasks to make it more readable.

4. Implement the extra packages needed in test-requirements.txt instead
   of trying to use a task to install them, because doing it in Ansible
   makes understanding the venv in relation to the inventory complicated..

5. Move the vars_files argument to the top of the play to make it easier
   to find and more uniform with other plays in OSA.

6. Switch from using octavia_ansible_endpoint_type to a hard-coded
   endpoint, then remove the octavia_ansible_endpoint_type var.

7. Switch from using the 'endpoint_type' argument for the openstack
   modules to using the more modern 'interface' argument.

8. Remove the 'run_once' argument on the 'Upload key to nova' task
   because only localhost is targeted, so the argument is moot.

9. Remove the 'Set VIP fact' task in favor of just using the 'vip_output'
   register in the 'Test the Listener' task. Setting a fact is pointless.

10. To help the existing patches pass, we add python-pip to the distro
    packages. This will be reverted later once the required changes
    to remove this requirement have merged.

Depends-On: https://review.openstack.org/589248
Change-Id: I46962090f7baf4227e838e125fd318245f2bcb85
(cherry picked from commit bd9f0c0723a8a4720eafc939530d606feaff226e)

commit_message:
Update UPPER_CONSTRAINTS_FILE for stable/rocky

The new stable upper-constraints file is only available
after the openstack/requirements repository is branched.
This will happen around the RC1 timeframe.

Recheck and merge this change once the requirements
repository has been branched.

The CI system will work with this patch before the requirements
repository is branched because zuul configues the job to run
with a local copy of the file and defaults to the master branch.
However, accepting the patch will break the test configuration
on developers' local systems, so please wait until after the
requirements repository is branched to merge the patch.

Change-Id: I0a8ce28b16ac4b25b1b0af0c04db36bd82311fd1

commit_message:
Update UPPER_CONSTRAINTS_FILE for stable/rocky

The new stable upper-constraints file is only available
after the openstack/requirements repository is branched.
This will happen around the RC1 timeframe.

Recheck and merge this change once the requirements
repository has been branched.

The CI system will work with this patch before the requirements
repository is branched because zuul configues the job to run
with a local copy of the file and defaults to the master branch.
However, accepting the patch will break the test configuration
on developers' local systems, so please wait until after the
requirements repository is branched to merge the patch.

Change-Id: I3a3a683dd4de5b051f56a4fd1708759f20babecc

commit_message:
Set quota for octavia service project

The default quotas are often not sufficient for a side wide
load balancing service. This will adjust them to some more
reasonable values.

The os_quota module of ansible assumes an installed
block storage service so it is not suitable for our
tests which don't install cinder. Therefore we
are using the openstack client straight.

Backport note:
Due to changes in master, this is not a clean cherry-pick.
This patch is a re-implementation in a slightly different
way.

Change-Id: If85cc3862b9316d9bf43e025bfaab8e1b7fd5576
(cherry picked from commit 3d0dfb706ca336351cc1f25a2afa55c665e02258)

commit_message:
Always start cinder API last

Cinder api was started last until a recent commit introduced a
regression by changing the order [1].

This reverts it.

[1]: https://github.com/openstack/openstack-ansible-os_cinder/commit/12ea9635ff5f4d4dd9eee068e7ce27fb84a52846

Change-Id: Iba0c0c170e6bb8f1b9e414ddad3426dd777ab894

commit_message:
Using isinstance(f, collections.Callable)

global function callable(f) is removed in python3.
It can be replaced with isinstance(f, collections.Callable)

This patch addresses the change.

Ref : https://docs.python.org/3.1/whatsnew/3.0.html

Change-Id: I61be865c40eb64a700feabd6c9ad2d2d41b4b32c

commit_message:
Use the TESTING_BRANCH env var for constraints

The TESTING_BRANCH environment variable is provided by the
run_tests.sh script and is derived from the .gitreview file.

This ensures that once the master branch becomes a stable
branch, the constraints from the stable branch in the
integrated repository will automatically get used once the
.gitreview file is updated.

To ensure that the required environment variables are present
we export them appropriately in run_tests.sh and modify the
tox configuration to pass them into the tox test.

Change-Id: If187e7d76d3b9e918debdf78a189e8bd87a8fb31
Needed-By: https://review.openstack.org/579371
